### [Proverbs Chapter 15](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#001.md)

[Proverbs 15:2](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">pro 15:2</span></span>

Aright - Expressing what he knows prudently and gracefully. Poureth out
- Plentifully, continually, and vehemently, as a fountain does waters.

[Proverbs 15:4](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">pro 15:4</span></span>

Wholesome - Which utters sound and useful counsels. Tree of life - Is
greatly useful to preserve the present life, and to promote the
spiritual and eternal life, both of the speaker and hearers.
Perverseness - False or corrupt speeches. A breach - Disturbs and wounds
the spirits, both of the speaker and hearers.

[Proverbs 15:6](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">pro 15:6</span></span>

Revenues - Though he may obtain great revenues, yet they are attended
with much trouble.

[Proverbs 15:7](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">pro 15:7</span></span>

Disperse - Freely communicate to others what they know.

[Proverbs 15:8](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#008.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_008">pro 15:8</span></span>

Sacrifice - All the religious services, yea, the most costly; one kind
being put for all the rest. Prayer - The cheapest and meanest services.

[Proverbs 15:11](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#011.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_011">pro 15:11</span></span>

Destruction - The place of destruction, of which men know nothing but by
Divine revelation.

[Proverbs 15:14](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#014.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_014">pro 15:14</span></span>

Foolishness - Wickedness is meat and drink to them.

[Proverbs 15:15](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#015.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_015">pro 15:15</span></span>

Afflicted - Of the troubled in mind. Evil - Tedious and uncomfortable.
Chearful - Heb. of a good heart.

[Proverbs 15:16](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#016.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_016">pro 15:16</span></span>

Trouble - Tumultuous lusts and passions, vexatious cares, and horrors of
conscience.

[Proverbs 15:19](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#019.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_019">pro 15:19</span></span>

An hedge - As a way hedged up with thorns, troublesome, perplexed, and
full of difficulties. Plain - Is easy and pleasant to him,
notwithstanding all its difficulties.

[Proverbs 15:22](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#022.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_022">pro 15:22</span></span>

Counsel - When men do not seek, or will not receive advice from others.

[Proverbs 15:23](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#023.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_023">pro 15:23</span></span>

The answer - By a wise, or good and seasonable answer.

[Proverbs 15:24](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#024.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_024">pro 15:24</span></span>

The way - The way a wise man takes to obtain life, is to place his
heart, and treasure, and conversation on things above.

[Proverbs 15:25](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#025.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_025">pro 15:25</span></span>

The proud - Of the mighty oppressors. The border - The estate, the
border being often used, for the land within the borders.

[Proverbs 15:26](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#026.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_026">pro 15:26</span></span>

Pleasant - Acceptable to God.

[Proverbs 15:27](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#027.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_027">pro 15:27</span></span>

Troubleth - Brings God's curse upon himself and family. Gifts - Bribes
given to corrupt judgment. Live - Shall preserve himself and family from
ruin.

[Proverbs 15:28](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#028.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_028">pro 15:28</span></span>

Studieth - He speaks considerately. The mouth - Not the heart; for he
rashly speaks what comes into his mouth, without the direction of his
heart or conscience.

[Proverbs 15:30](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#030.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_030">pro 15:30</span></span>

A good report - A good name. Fat - Not only chears a man for the
present, but gives him such stable comfort as revives his soul, and
gives vigour to his body.

[Proverbs 15:31](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#031.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_031">pro 15:31</span></span>

The ear - The man that hearkens to that reproof which leads to life,
seeks and delights in the company of the wise.

[Proverbs 15:33](../../../bib/kjv/pro015.htm#033.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_033">pro 15:33</span></span>

The instruction - Doth instruct men in true wisdom.

